article.description: — Avery Brown's 13 points helped Columbia defeat Temple 78-73 on Saturday.
article.headline: Brown, Columbia takes down Temple 78-73
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- — Avery Brown's 13 points helped Columbia defeat Temple 78-73 on Saturday. Brown also contributed five assists for the Lions (3-2). Jaden Cooper scored 11 points and added five rebounds. Geronimo Rubio De La Rosa was 3 of 8 shooting, including 2 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 4 from the line to finish with 11 points. Hysier Miller led the Owls (3-1) in scoring, finishing with 29 points and six assists. Matteo Picarelli added 18 points for Temple. In addition, Jahlil White finished with 11 points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
